If I could have given zero stars I would have done so. Non-existent reception, more than questionable hygiene, the floor slips and sticks, the receptionist couldn't even write my first name correctly. The bad points: obsolete and dangerous infrastructure, review the reception capacity, hygiene to review, lack of games for children under 3 years old.

One word: (sorry for the term!) DISGUSTING!!!! Lots of waste everywhere, tables, benches and chairs very dirty, sticky. Waste, pieces of cake, paper, tissues, and even empty juice briquettes everywhere in the play structure. The baby corner, no respect.... the 15 year olds are lying there and on their cell phones, others are bickering without paying any attention to the little ones. Apparently, if I understood correctly, there are park regulars... wow! No respect for the children or the parents who let everything happen! Music of a single, very strong style. And to top it off, the 3 clogged toilets which had overflowed on the floor, and all over the floor.. The person who cleans, sincerely, good luck.. he was running everywhere. And....no one wore the mask. Rather seen as a disgusting picnic, than a welcoming place with a fee! Nobody enforces the rules!  Your child is more in danger than safe! Finally, everyone keeps their shoes on, (except in the structures) people walked everywhere mm on the foam mats to go see their children. All black socks from black!!!!!! Horrible. And.. they play with their hands when mm to climb and everything. Anyway. I would never go back there. I have done others, much better ones where the rules and instructions are respected.
